nl_problem:
# Task: longest_common_subsequence
# Interface:
Class: Solution
Method: longestCommonSubsequence(self, arg1, arg2)

Given two strings text1 and text2, return the length of their longest common subsequence.
A subsequence of a string is a new string generated from the original string with some characters (can be none) deleted without changing the relative order of the remaining characters.
For example, "ace" is a subsequence of "abcde".
A common subsequence of two strings is a subsequence that is common to both strings.
If there is no common subsequence, return 0.

Constraints:
- 1 <= text1.length, text2.length <= 1000
- text1 and text2 consist of only lowercase English characters.
lisp_spec:
(task
  (name "longest_common_subsequence")
  (signature ( (text1 string) (text2 string) ) int)
  (constraints
    (constraint "1 <= length(text1), length(text2) <= 1000")
    (constraint "text1 and text2 consist of only lowercase English characters")
  )
  (goal
    (description "Return the length of the longest common subsequence between two strings.")
    (rule "A subsequence is a new string generated from the original string with some characters deleted without changing the relative order of the remaining characters.")
    (rule "A common subsequence is a subsequence that is common to both strings.")
    (return "The length of the longest common subsequence. If there is no common subsequence, return 0.")
  )
)
